1.text: Apply your base before your blush.

2.text: Lightly sweep your brush through your powdered blush.

3.text: Dot and blend liquid blush with your finger.

5.text: Apply blush to a heart-shaped face in a “C” shape.

6.text: Avoid the apples of your cheeks if your face is round.

7.text: Go from the cheekbone to the temple if your face is more oval.

8.text: Apply blush in a circular motion if you have a square face.

9.text: Buy a baby pink, peach, or sheer plum color if you’re fair-skinned.

10.text: Use an apricot or mauve color if you have a medium skin tone.

11.text: Get a rose or bronze-colored blush if you’re olive-skinned.

12.text: Opt for raisin, brick, or bright tangerine if you have a dark complexion.

13.text: Use a powder blush if you have normal to oily skin.

14.text: Go with a cream blush if you have dry or aging skin.
